menu "breadboard: bb_serialize_json"

config BB_SERIALIZE_JSON_F64_DECIMALS
    int "Fixed fractional digits for f64 JSON output"
    default 6
    range 1 15
    help
        Number of fractional digits emitted for double values
        (deterministic fixed-decimal, e.g. 3.5 -> "3.500000" at the
        default of 6). No snprintf/locale involved -- purely a scale-
        and-round hand-rolled formatter.

config BB_SERIALIZE_JSON_SCRATCH_MAX_BYTES
    int "Shared key/number/literal reassembly scratch size (bytes) for the JSON scanner"
    default 64
    range 16 256
    help
        Size of the single internal scratch buffer the streaming/bounded
        JSON scanner (bb_serialize_json_scan_*) uses to reassemble a
        key string plus the number or literal that immediately follows
        it -- the only token kinds ever fully buffered (string VALUES
        stream as spans and never touch this buffer). A key or number
        that would overflow this bound fails the scan with
        BB_ERR_NO_SPACE rather than truncating silently.

endmenu
